def: A writ commanding the sheriff to distrain a person by his goodsor chattels, to compel a compliance with something required of him.
One who does not belong, or refuses to belong, to a tradesunion.
Having spars smaller than the usual dimension; -- said ofvessels.
A binary compound of nitrogen with a more metallic element orradical; as, boric nitride.
Lack of proper digestive action; a failure of the normalchanges which food should undergo in the alimentary canal; dyspepsia;incomplete or difficult digestion.
